WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:01.417
Hey, good morning, family.

00:00:01.417 --> 00:00:03.575
Thank you for joining us today.

00:00:03.575 --> 00:00:08.096
Well, it's Diana and I again, and I'm excited she's with me today.

00:00:08.096 --> 00:00:11.519
My best friend is with me—my hottie.

00:00:13.964 --> 00:00:18.020
After all these years, I'm still smitten over this girl.

00:00:18.020 --> 00:00:22.502
She is my best friend, and I'm so thankful that she's with me.

00:00:22.502 --> 00:00:23.555
Best friend, too.

00:00:23.555 --> 00:00:25.732
We're here at our spot.

00:00:25.732 --> 00:00:29.680
I come here because it inspires me.

00:00:30.560 --> 00:00:35.689
I know I've said this before, folks, but I love the ORU campus.

00:00:35.689 --> 00:00:38.342
Make no little plans here.

00:00:38.342 --> 00:00:43.836
God is about to show up and show off at this campus.

00:00:43.836 --> 00:00:54.559
There was a lady that sent us a flyer in the mail about all the revivals that are taking place across the nation on college campuses.

00:00:54.821 --> 00:01:00.559
Whenever she sent that to me, I guess she was saying, 'Hey, look, it's happening other places.

00:01:00.559 --> 00:01:18.789
' But I'm telling you, this will be the mega-revival at this school with Victory across the street there—big victory with Paul Daugherty.

00:01:25.145 --> 00:01:25.786
I believe we're about to see one of the greatest revivals this world has ever seen.

00:01:25.786 --> 00:01:32.360
People say, 'Hey, Brandon, what do you do for a living?

00:01:32.360 --> 00:01:38.017
' and everything, and want to know what Diana and I do.

00:01:42.479 --> 00:01:42.799
Do you all work?

00:01:42.799 --> 00:01:49.013
Yes, we do eBay and Poshmark, and we continue to do that.

00:01:54.427 --> 00:01:54.640
It's made a good living for us, and we're thankful for it.

00:01:54.640 --> 00:02:11.970
We find stuff at thrift stores and we go into these thrift stores and we buy used stuff, and we turn it around for a profit.

00:02:11.970 --> 00:02:15.452
We'll continue to do that.

00:02:27.792 --> 00:02:28.680
We enjoy doing it.

00:02:29.415 --> 00:02:34.020
We like working together and we'll continue to work there.

00:02:34.020 --> 00:02:47.560
Who wants to work for the world if you can work for yourself and make better money than you do for the world?

00:02:47.560 --> 00:02:52.920
I think it's pretty smart on our part.

00:02:52.920 --> 00:02:54.690
God led us.

00:02:54.690 --> 00:03:04.623
Diana is the one that came up with the idea through the Holy Spirit, and the Lord shows me where to go and Diana goes in and gets it.

00:03:04.623 --> 00:03:19.730
That's the way we've done it, and that's how I've practiced His presence: listening to Him for ideas of how to get wealth.

00:03:19.730 --> 00:03:29.119
I don't just sit there and wait idly by saying, 'God, where's my blessing?

00:03:29.119 --> 00:03:39.594
' I go out and take the land, and we take it by force, don't we, babe?

00:03:39.594 --> 00:03:49.315
We're not going to sit back and just wait for a mailbox miracle.

00:03:49.315 --> 00:03:56.159
Lottery mentality—now if the Lord wants to bring it that way, fine.

00:03:56.159 --> 00:04:02.640
Like I've told her, we believe in being debt-free and living that way.

00:04:11.012 --> 00:04:12.377
If God doesn't provide it, we don't have it.

00:04:12.377 --> 00:04:22.420
We believe that God is the one that abundantly supplies every need we have, and that's the way we've lived our life.

00:04:22.420 --> 00:04:29.933
We go and find stuff and we can flip it on Craigslist or Facebook Marketplace.

00:04:29.933 --> 00:04:33.489
There are creative ideas to do things.

00:04:33.489 --> 00:04:43.769
When we come to ORU and we sit out here, it's because we know what's coming.

00:04:43.769 --> 00:04:57.150
What the Lord has told us—we know that building is going to be filled to capacity, the Mabee Center over there.

00:05:00.095 --> 00:05:00.400
Is that what it's called?

00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:02.754
Yeah, the Mabee Center.

00:05:02.754 --> 00:05:10.960
Yes, we believe that building is going to be filled to capacity with the fire.

00:05:11.458 --> 00:05:15.890
The Holy Ghost fire is going to be over that building.

00:05:15.890 --> 00:05:24.590
Now you say, 'Brandon, you spoke so poorly about Florida and about these other areas.

00:05:24.590 --> 00:05:27.479
' Folks, I'm just being real with you.

00:05:32.514 --> 00:05:38.194
I don't mean to be offensive to anybody and where you live, but I'm just real.

00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:45.160
I tell you what I feel when I go into your area.

00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:47.960
Now, can you change it?

00:05:47.960 --> 00:05:55.056
Was I saying, 'Oh, we got to run from the demonic, you got to leave Miami?

00:05:55.056 --> 00:05:56.687
' No.

00:05:56.687 --> 00:06:14.968
God did not station me there, and He will equip who He's called there to deal with what's there.

00:06:32.123 --> 00:06:32.488
I believe you if you say, 'Well, I don't feel it because I'm here.

00:06:32.488 --> 00:06:44.199
' Well, God's called you to be there, but He didn't call me to be there.

00:06:44.199 --> 00:06:50.234
So He didn't tell me to go in.

00:06:50.234 --> 00:06:53.240
It's like going into somebody's backyard.

00:06:53.240 --> 00:07:17.875
Me as a prophetic voice saying, 'I'm going to go into your backyard and take authority over what's going on'—He didn't give me authority there to do that.

00:07:17.875 --> 00:07:20.760
He didn't assign me there.

00:07:22.356 --> 00:07:33.880
I was there on vacation with my family to go to Billy Burke and to listen to him because I want impartation.

00:07:55.520 --> 00:08:11.231
I'm wanting to learn how to flow in the healing anointing because, as I told Diana, there's not a lot of elders in the church that take the time to impart into the younger generation, so you have to learn it by trial and error.

00:08:12.230 --> 00:08:17.140
A lot of what we've learned is through trial and error.

00:08:17.140 --> 00:08:32.165
There are times, like I've told you all with Megan, whenever I had that visitation from the Lord, He took me back in the past.

00:08:32.165 --> 00:08:45.540
I was complaining about the shots and the things that I had done through the flu vaccination, and three weeks later Megan was not able to talk.

00:08:52.627 --> 00:09:02.000
I remember I was telling the Lord—He could hear my heart—I said, 'Man, if I could just go back to the past and change the decisions I've made.

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:15.068
If I could just have a moment to tell my younger self, "Don't get the flu shot, don't do these things for Megan.

00:09:15.068 --> 00:09:21.617
"' Because I didn't know she was going to have an allergic reaction to it.

00:09:21.617 --> 00:09:26.223
I didn't know all that stuff.

00:09:32.960 --> 00:09:44.621
But I thought in my mind all the time, and when the Lord woke me up and He took me out of my body, He took me back to my past.

00:09:44.621 --> 00:09:49.480
He showed me the power of a decision.

00:09:49.480 --> 00:09:57.285
But He also showed me how that decision changed me for the better.

00:09:57.285 --> 00:10:07.984
Then He told me, 'You're not big enough, Brandon, with your past decisions to mess up you and Diana's life.

00:10:07.984 --> 00:10:25.513
' He said, 'The steps of the righteous are ordered by the Lord, and what the devil meant for bad, I will turn around for good in your favor.

00:10:25.748 --> 00:10:30.646
I did not cause this with your daughter, Brandon.

00:10:30.646 --> 00:10:42.959
The devil comes to kill, steal, and destroy, but I'm going to turn it around for good for you.

00:10:42.959 --> 00:11:03.460
' All the pressure, all the stuff that you've gone through in the past will shape you into what you need to be for the future if you do not adopt a victim mentality.

00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:11.560
Do not allow your circumstances from your past to dictate your future.

00:11:16.395 --> 00:11:17.840
I will not allow the circumstance of what I have been through to dictate my tomorrow.

00:11:17.840 --> 00:11:23.537
I'm not going to be a victim; I'm a victor.

00:11:23.537 --> 00:11:28.839
We've said that over and over and over again.

00:11:28.839 --> 00:11:53.140
Whenever I saw the power of a choice and a decision displayed in front of my face—how the pressure of raising a child with special needs and autism has changed me and changed Diana for the better—I realized God's on your side.

00:11:53.140 --> 00:12:00.983
Whatever you have been through, always stay on God's side.

00:12:00.983 --> 00:12:10.347
Even if you don't understand why you're going through it, always stay on God's side.

00:12:10.347 --> 00:12:22.023
My favorite saying is, 'God is a good God and the devil is a bad devil.

00:12:22.023 --> 00:12:36.679
' Oral Roberts—just like what we're here at his university—it's such a beautiful university where, you know, 'Make no little plans in life, believing God for big.

00:12:36.679 --> 00:12:42.319
' I'm going to tell you, a lot of people get mad.

00:12:42.319 --> 00:12:45.948
They say, 'Well, you got a nice car.

00:12:45.948 --> 00:12:48.987
' Of course I believe God for big!

00:12:48.987 --> 00:12:51.720
You believe God for favor.

00:12:51.720 --> 00:12:57.779
We have favor at the dealership; we have favor wherever you go.

00:13:04.822 --> 00:13:05.204
You sow a seed for it.

00:13:05.204 --> 00:13:12.794
We keep selling on eBay and we grow our business.

00:13:12.794 --> 00:13:20.040
I'm never going to embrace poverty, folks.

00:13:20.040 --> 00:13:37.764
So if you don't want to see me get blessed, don't watch this channel, because this is just the beginning.

00:13:46.577 --> 00:13:49.566
I believe it's time for exceedingly, abundantly above all that you dare ask or think.

00:14:01.458 --> 00:14:28.547
I believe that the things that the Lord has spoken to me prophetically when I pray and intercede about the end-time wealth transfer—it's not for me to just stay where we were with eBay and Poshmark, and my wife sitting there typing all night and looking for things in the thrift stores.

00:14:28.547 --> 00:14:33.719
I'm not going to do that forever.

00:14:33.719 --> 00:14:46.286
Right now we do it, but there will be an expiration date to that.

00:14:48.480 --> 00:15:03.114
The Lord's already told us there'll be a day when this stops, but right now it's what He wants us to do, and we're thankful for it.

00:15:03.114 --> 00:15:17.686
Wherever God stations you, whatever God puts you to do, always do it with a joyful attitude and a good heart.

00:15:17.686 --> 00:15:31.480
Don't complain your way through it, because the more you complain, even in your heart, you'll stay there until you get your heart right.

00:15:31.480 --> 00:15:46.089
I've learned if you want promotion from the Lord, you've got to be faithful with the little and God will make you ruler over much.

00:15:46.089 --> 00:16:05.513
Say, 'God, no matter where I'm at, no matter what I'm doing—cleaning toilets or cleaning stains out of a garment that I found at a thrift store—I'm thankful.

00:16:05.513 --> 00:16:18.667
' I remember before when I was living on food stamps, and I'm thankful, Father, for this garment.

00:16:18.667 --> 00:16:41.213
Yeah, it's a Burberry or whatever I found today that has a coffee stain on it, but Lord, give me an anointing to get that coffee stain out.

00:16:41.213 --> 00:16:49.503
Give me an anointing to get that ketchup stain out.

00:16:49.503 --> 00:16:59.285
He has taught me how to do things, and we've learned how to get stains out.

00:16:59.285 --> 00:17:01.239
It's pretty cool.

00:17:01.239 --> 00:17:05.720
But it's hearing His voice.

00:17:11.739 --> 00:17:15.699
You say, 'Well, I don't hear the voice of the Lord.

00:17:15.699 --> 00:17:23.582
' I don't believe you.

00:17:32.160 --> 00:17:36.600
The Bible says we will hear the Good Shepherd's voice, and a stranger's voice we will not follow.

00:17:37.480 --> 00:17:39.875
I believe the Bible more than I believe you.

00:17:49.919 --> 00:17:50.504
You know why you don't hear Him?

00:17:59.760 --> 00:18:00.400
Because you have too much of yourself in the way.

00:18:00.400 --> 00:18:13.787
If you say you don't hear the voice of the Lord, it's because you've got too much self.

00:18:13.787 --> 00:18:21.430
Every believer has the opportunity to hear the voice of the Lord.

00:18:21.430 --> 00:18:27.380
A child can hear the voice of the Lord.

00:18:27.380 --> 00:18:32.799
Die to self daily and listen to Him.

00:18:32.799 --> 00:18:37.508
Be filled with and controlled by the Spirit.

00:18:37.508 --> 00:18:40.860
There's no shortcuts, is there, babe?

00:18:40.860 --> 00:18:51.519
We were talking to somebody the other day and Diana said, 'Brandon, they didn't hear anything you said.

00:18:51.519 --> 00:19:00.853
' She said they wanted an easy way; they wanted a shortcut.

00:19:00.853 --> 00:19:02.451
There's no shortcuts.

00:19:02.451 --> 00:19:07.346
You can discern whether they're receiving or not.

00:19:07.346 --> 00:19:13.180
Within 15 minutes, the Lord always shows me if they're receiving or if they're not.

00:19:13.180 --> 00:19:21.937
Either you catch it or you don't, but there's no shortcuts.

00:19:21.937 --> 00:19:28.044
There's only hard work, and anything worth doing is worth doing well.

00:19:28.044 --> 00:19:33.147
This is the only body that you're ever going to have.

00:19:33.147 --> 00:19:42.200
People want six-packs, but they don't want to go to the gym.

00:19:53.739 --> 00:19:53.919
I'm speaking of me.

00:19:53.919 --> 00:20:04.617
I'd love to look like Arnold Schwarzenegger, but it takes a lot of work to look like him.

00:20:15.960 --> 00:20:16.360
It takes work to eat right and exercise.

00:20:16.360 --> 00:20:25.307
Everybody has the same ability, the same 24 hours, the same seven days a week.

00:20:25.307 --> 00:20:32.995
You can be a spiritual giant in the spirit realm if you just put forth the effort to get there.

00:20:41.080 --> 00:20:41.352
God is no respecter of persons.

00:20:41.352 --> 00:20:57.200
What He did for Oral Roberts, for Katherine Kuhlman, for Billy Joe Daugherty, for Paul Daugherty across the street—what He did for them, He'll do for you.

00:20:57.200 --> 00:21:02.030
How big is your 'want-to' for change in your life?

00:21:17.159 --> 00:21:17.519
Do you want it bad enough to do what they did to get it?

00:21:17.519 --> 00:21:18.959
They sacrificed.

00:21:18.959 --> 00:21:27.860
They believed in the spiritual laws that whatsoever a man sows, that will he also reap.

00:21:32.773 --> 00:21:38.578
I come here because I'm inspired that this is somebody's faith in action.

00:21:38.578 --> 00:21:44.445
Faith without works is dead, the Bible says.

00:21:44.445 --> 00:21:48.120
This is faith manifested.

00:21:48.120 --> 00:21:54.400
I see these buildings—started as a seed, started as a field.

00:21:54.400 --> 00:22:15.799
He was believing God for just this land and the farmer wouldn't sell it to him, but look: the vision from here produced all these buildings.

00:22:15.799 --> 00:22:19.120
It produced the church across the street.

00:22:19.120 --> 00:22:26.759
Paul Daugherty and them just latched onto the vision of this man.

00:22:37.022 --> 00:22:38.050
If you ever want to read about his testimony about all of ORU, it's in *The Ultimate Voice* by Oral Roberts.

00:22:38.050 --> 00:22:40.750
Oh, phenomenal book.

00:22:40.750 --> 00:22:51.720
Speaking about hearing God's voice, he talks about his testimony of ORU and how the miracle started.

00:22:51.720 --> 00:22:56.839
It's really a great book to read—life-changing.

00:22:58.235 --> 00:23:02.120
I was praying for ministers and the Lord spoke to me.

00:23:02.120 --> 00:23:11.435
I was praying for my son and always praying for your kids' future and for a godly spouse.

00:23:11.435 --> 00:23:15.394
Intercede for your children to find the right mate.

00:23:23.270 --> 00:23:23.440
I was driving around recently and the Lord spoke to me.

00:23:35.336 --> 00:23:35.628
He said, 'Brandon, many of My ministers have married a Delilah.

00:23:38.658 --> 00:23:59.297
I warned them and warned them not to marry certain individuals, and they marry them either out of lust of the eye, lust of the flesh, or whatever, and they're snared by a Delilah, just like Samson was.

00:23:59.297 --> 00:24:17.520
' I saw ministers trying to take off like a rocket because they had all this potential inside of them, but they had a rock—the Delilah—attached to the neck of the rocket.

00:24:17.520 --> 00:24:36.190
In the vision, I saw the rocket trying to take off, but it was only allowed to go so far because they were attached to a major rock called a Delilah.

00:24:36.190 --> 00:24:54.474
If you marry a Delilah—and the Bible says do not be unequally yoked with unbelievers—you have to link yourself up with somebody who is there to help you; iron sharpens iron.

00:24:54.474 --> 00:25:00.220
This was my warning to you young people: do not marry a Delilah.

00:25:04.004 --> 00:25:04.784
Do not marry an Ishmael; look for your Isaac.

00:25:09.620 --> 00:25:16.235
The devil will try to bring an Ishmael to you to try to get your ministry to not make it.

00:25:16.235 --> 00:25:20.760
You'll always be struggling, married to a Delilah.

00:25:20.760 --> 00:25:35.335
Now, if you married your Delilah, I believe there's still hope and that God will turn around what the enemy meant for bad.

00:25:35.335 --> 00:25:41.488
Some people just don't have it and they don't want it.

00:25:58.949 --> 00:25:59.099
They like the fame, they like the celebrity, they like the finances, but they're not there for the right reasons.

00:25:59.099 --> 00:26:02.792
So I warn you: don't marry a Delilah.

00:26:08.535 --> 00:26:21.720
The Lord has spoken to me and He said, 'Many of My ministers, Brandon, were called to go even higher than what they are, but they married the wrong people.

00:26:21.720 --> 00:26:28.080
' Now, you say, 'Should I divorce them?

00:26:28.080 --> 00:26:30.587
' Heavens no.

00:26:30.587 --> 00:26:33.711
I'm not trying to advocate that.

00:26:34.760 --> 00:26:35.420
You pray for them.

00:26:37.818 --> 00:26:42.480
You made a choice, you made a covenant, so now you have integrity and you intercede.

00:26:42.480 --> 00:26:45.680
It just could have been an easier path.

00:26:45.680 --> 00:27:01.175
I'm trying to tell you, if you're single and the Lord is warning you today: listen to the voice of the Lord.

00:27:01.175 --> 00:27:08.387
Life has obstacles, and it matters who you link yourself up with.

00:27:09.360 --> 00:27:25.066
You don't want to be dragging a Delilah behind you while God says, 'Get up to the summit.

00:27:25.066 --> 00:27:33.799
' Be very vigilant about this because this is a tactic of the enemy.

00:27:35.709 --> 00:27:40.460
The devil will send an Ishmael; the devil will send a Delilah.

00:27:43.800 --> 00:27:52.560
You have to say, 'Who's in your life that's cutting your hair and trying to gouge out your eyes?

00:27:52.560 --> 00:28:02.387
' stealing the vision of what God's called you to do.

00:28:02.387 --> 00:28:10.720
Find your Esther today; don't line up with your Delilah.

00:28:19.756 --> 00:28:20.044
I feel the power of the Lord on that today.

00:28:20.044 --> 00:28:29.050
There's some of you out there that God's trying to shake.

00:28:44.988 --> 00:28:45.480
It's time to believe God for big.

00:28:45.480 --> 00:28:47.399
Don't lose faith.

00:28:47.719 --> 00:28:52.755
You say, 'Well, I've messed up my life.

00:28:52.755 --> 00:29:04.848
I've derailed my life so much that God can't use me.

00:29:04.848 --> 00:29:31.799
' But the Lord told me to tell you: what the devil meant for bad and the traps you've been snared in—the very pit you've fallen into—God's going to deliver you out of them all if you just seek Him and repent.

00:29:31.799 --> 00:29:37.095
The best is yet to come.

00:29:39.432 --> 00:29:52.479
If you're single and you are believing God for a spouse, I would definitely recommend you to write a list—write your vision and make it plain.

00:29:53.779 --> 00:30:03.540
That's what Diana and I both did when we didn't even know each other.

00:30:08.352 --> 00:30:12.840
I made a very specific, detailed list of everything I was believing God for in a mate.

00:30:12.840 --> 00:30:15.713
He did the same thing.

00:30:15.713 --> 00:30:39.320
When we met, we got out our lists and read them to each other, and it was exactly—to a T—like I had written it about Brandon and he had written it about me.

00:30:40.205 --> 00:30:41.679
I believe it works.

00:30:50.709 --> 00:30:50.919
I believe that God will give you the desires of your heart.

00:30:55.071 --> 00:31:06.559
You can pray for your future spouse right now, that the Lord keeps them protected and set apart, that they're not being snared by wickedness and the lust and desires of the flesh, that they remain on fire for God.

00:31:06.559 --> 00:31:18.275
Any snares that the devil sends their way, they overcome them by the blood of the Lamb and by the word of their testimony.

00:31:18.275 --> 00:31:23.175
You've got to continue to do it.

00:31:30.262 --> 00:31:30.480
You don't just visit the anointing; you live there.

00:31:30.480 --> 00:31:34.079
Diana and I choose to live there.

00:31:34.079 --> 00:31:47.208
It's not convenient to drive so far over here to ORU—I live a long way from here—but I choose to do it to make this a habit.

00:31:47.208 --> 00:31:55.711
My son said when we went to Florida, 'Man, I missed going to ORU, Dad, because there's a presence there.

00:31:55.711 --> 00:32:02.569
' It blesses me because I believe in raising godly children and keeping them set apart for their spouse.

00:32:02.569 --> 00:32:04.171
Megan's back there; she hears.

00:32:04.171 --> 00:32:06.240
We're believing God for Megan.

00:32:08.768 --> 00:32:16.466
I hope this video inspired you to believe God to 'make no little plans here.

00:32:16.466 --> 00:32:23.839
' I love the little prayer tower over there.

00:32:23.839 --> 00:32:29.000
Diana and I are going to pray for you.

00:32:32.249 --> 00:32:33.227
I want you to believe God for bigger.

00:32:33.227 --> 00:32:38.084
Donald Trump has his meeting on Friday.

00:32:38.084 --> 00:32:46.609
Somebody called and said, 'Hey Brandon, did you know that there's a big crypto meeting on Friday?

00:32:46.609 --> 00:32:49.580
' Folks, we're at the point of liftoff.

00:32:49.580 --> 00:32:56.293
Something major is about to take place for the body of Christ.

00:32:56.293 --> 00:33:08.200
God is about to bring forth all the seeds that you've sowed in the past.

00:33:08.200 --> 00:33:23.331
You've got to take the seed that you have and plant it so that God has something to work with.

00:33:36.470 --> 00:33:36.775
If you do nothing, you're going to get nothing.

00:33:36.775 --> 00:33:42.063
Sew your time at your church!

00:33:42.063 --> 00:33:46.808
Volunteer, clean bathrooms, and believe God for a job.

00:33:46.808 --> 00:33:55.840
There's something you can do to sew your time at your local church.

00:34:07.839 --> 00:34:09.190
I remember when we had no seed to give, we had one hundred dollars that we needed for our electric bill.

00:34:17.818 --> 00:34:25.320
The Lord told Diana, 'Take that hundred dollars and go to the thrift store, and I'm going to teach you how to multiply that.

00:34:25.320 --> 00:34:28.799
' Once we started tithing, the miracles started happening.

00:34:28.799 --> 00:34:35.019
We always tithe first because you give to God first.

00:34:35.019 --> 00:34:47.472
I'll be real: we were once forced to tithe at our jobs at a church, and if you did not tithe, they fired you.

00:34:47.472 --> 00:34:57.080
My attitude was not happy about that at first, but it trained us.

00:35:01.819 --> 00:35:04.360
I told the Lord, 'You either take care of us or I quit.

00:35:04.360 --> 00:35:10.315
' And He told me, 'Brandon, I've called you to be here.

00:35:10.315 --> 00:35:14.310
I need you to pray for that man.

00:35:14.310 --> 00:35:23.703
' And He told me he was going to lose his church, and he did.

00:35:23.703 --> 00:35:32.068
But I stuck by what the Lord told me to do for thirteen years.

00:35:32.068 --> 00:35:38.645
We sacrificed making nothing, and then He started teaching me how to do things.

00:35:38.645 --> 00:35:47.653
When Diana came up with the idea of doing eBay and Poshmark, that's when our life started to change drastically.

00:35:52.693 --> 00:36:03.183
I could not see how used t-shirts at a thrift store could pay a bill, but come to find out, people wanted those shirts.

00:36:11.319 --> 00:36:11.652
They like those band tees.

00:36:11.652 --> 00:36:20.980
If the Lord tells you that shirt right there is a vintage t-shirt, sell it!

00:36:36.349 --> 00:36:39.062
It might look stinky with holes in it, but somebody wanted it.

00:36:39.062 --> 00:36:43.835
Whenever we started tithing, the miracles started happening.

00:36:48.839 --> 00:36:58.976
There was that one time when the children didn't have shoes, but that day I looked down and there was a twenty-dollar bill laying on the ground in my direct path.

00:36:58.976 --> 00:37:00.960
Praise God!

00:37:00.960 --> 00:37:04.240
That's how my God works.

00:37:21.048 --> 00:37:21.621
I walked in and they had a sale on the shoes, and that twenty dollars got the shoes the kids needed.

00:37:21.621 --> 00:37:25.759
Never forget the miracles from the past.

00:37:25.759 --> 00:37:33.684
We created a book of miracles just to smear it in the devil's face every day.

00:37:33.684 --> 00:37:43.950
Have a 'stacking rocks' experience to go back to and say, 'This is where God came through.

00:37:43.950 --> 00:37:52.142
' If He did it once, He will do it again.

00:37:54.905 --> 00:38:07.505
The devil's not afraid of you having one miracle; what he's afraid of is you having multiple miracles—volumes of them.

00:38:22.035 --> 00:38:27.108
I remember the time Tim came up and said, 'Brandon, I don't know why, but my wife, Janet, said the Lord told us to give you a thousand dollars.

00:38:27.108 --> 00:38:30.097
' I almost passed out.

00:38:30.097 --> 00:38:37.693
It was a shock and awe moment on December 22nd.

00:38:37.693 --> 00:38:52.394
We were not going to go out and ask, because we're not in the ministry of 'dropping hints,' but He came through.

00:38:52.394 --> 00:38:56.800
That's one of my stacking rocks moments.

00:38:56.800 --> 00:39:04.000
We're just real; we have issues, folks, but we choose to focus on Jesus.

00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:07.995
Our marriage gets stronger because of it.

00:39:07.995 --> 00:39:13.760
We pray together, we fast together, we take communion together as a family.

00:39:21.960 --> 00:39:22.340
We spend hours in the car and we pray.

00:39:22.340 --> 00:39:29.200
Whoever gets this car next is going to have a glory car!

00:39:31.360 --> 00:39:39.236
I just wanted to tell you today that you're not big enough to derail your life.

00:39:39.236 --> 00:39:46.480
What the devil has done to try to derail your life, God's going to turn around for good.

00:39:46.480 --> 00:39:50.080
If you're seeking Him daily, God's going to move big.

00:39:50.080 --> 00:40:04.578
